\cos'(x) = \lim\limits_{ h\to 0}\frac{\cos(x+h)-\cos(x)}{h}
\cos(x+h) = \cos(x)\cos(h) - \sin(x)\sin(h)
\Rightarrow \cos'(x) = \lim\limits_{h\to0}\frac{\cos(x)(\cos(h)-1) - \sin(x)\sin(h)}{h}
= -\sin(x)
